From e1404c55d59b8bae80e2ffbd60a891b147bc7f39 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Hoffman <alxhoff@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:01:01 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 09/12] camera/vi: Add D4xx embedded-metadata channel and GMSL
 plumbing (JP7)

VI-core support for the RealSense D4xx GMSL2 stack, ported from JP5
(0004/0028) and adapted to kernel 6.8:

- mc_common.[hc]: embedded-metadata channel (MAX_CHANNELS, struct embedded,
  dser/ser device pointers) and nvidia,gmsl-dser/ser-device DT parsing
- channel.c/graph.c/vi5_fops.c: metadata video device (open/close, querycap,
  fmt/ioctl/queue ops), embedded-buffer release, graph init/cleanup hooks
- sensor_common.c: grey_y8 (V4L2_PIX_FMT_GREY) and grey_y16 (V4L2_PIX_FMT_Y16)
- tegra_camera_core.h: 64-byte stride alignment, EMBEDDED_8/USER_1..4 data types

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
